pipeline_summary.name: RunELT_Alert
pipeline_summary.description: Sequential ELT pipeline that builds analytics tables in Snowflake using CTAS operations, with data validation, atomic swaps, and Slack failure notifications.

components.name: Run CTAS to Build Analytics Tables
components.description: Executes a CTAS query to create analytics tables from raw Snowflake tables, validates that the temporary table contains rows, and atomically swaps the temporary table into production.
inputs: table_params (dictionary with schema, table name, and SQL query)

upstream_policy.description: First task in the pipeline; no upstream dependencies.

components.name: Slack Failure Notification
components.description: Sends a Slack alert when a pipeline task fails, using the configured onfailure callback.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when any preceding task reports a failure.

description.default: Sequential ELT pipeline that builds analytics tables in Snowflake using CTAS operations, with data validation, atomic swaps, and Slack failure notifications.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

table_params.description: Dictionary containing schema, table name, and SQL query for the CTAS operation.

sinks: analytics.mau_summary (and other analytics tables) in Snowflake
intermediate_datasets: analytics.temp_mau_summary (temporary tables used for atomic swaps)
